Repsol to Start Boiler at Bilbao Refinery in Spain, to Halt CG1

-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 
2011-05-12T10:52:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/repsol-to-start-boiler-at-bilbao-refinery-in-spain-to-halt-cg1.html
Repsol YPF SA (REP) ,  Spain ’s biggest oil
company, planned to start a boiler at its Petronor refinery in
Bilbao, Spain, while stopping a cogeneration plant.  The refinery was starting the BL12 boiler and subsequently
stopping the CG1 cogeneration unit, according to a statement
yesterday on Petronor’s  website .  The refinery has the capacity to process 220,000 barrels of
crude a day, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Repsol,
based in  Madrid , has carried out maintenance so far this year on
an alkylation unit, a platformer, two desulfurization plants, a
boiler and cogeneration facility, according to statements posted
on Petronor’s website.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
 nbakhsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  